# Project Source of Truth

Before answering, planning, or editing **any** file in this repo, read and follow:

| Priority | File | Scope |
|----------|------|-------|
| 1 | `AGENTS.md` | Architecture, conventions, git workflow, what to avoid |
| 2 | `design.md` | Visual language: editorial × Swiss × dark, typography, spacing, no rounded, no cards |
| 3 | `README.md` | Project summary, quick start, high-level scope |

## Rules

- **Read first** — If you have not read these files in the current session, read them before making changes.
- **Conflict resolution** — `design.md` wins for UI/visual decisions; `AGENTS.md` wins for code structure and agent behavior; `README.md` wins for project description and setup.
- **Stay consistent** — New components, styles, and copy must match all three. If code diverges from `design.md`, refactor toward the design spec (see "Current vs Target" in `design.md`).
- **Update docs** — When changing architecture or design tokens, update the relevant doc in the same task.
- **Branch context** — Default branch is `theme-2` (dark-only). See `AGENTS.md` for branch notes.

## Do not

- Ignore `design.md` anti-patterns (rounded corners, card UI, shadows on content).
- Contradict section system or animation pipeline defined in `AGENTS.md`.
- Introduce dependencies or patterns not aligned with the README tech stack without user approval.
